[These cases are not surprising since South Korea is within the endemic area of Japanese encephalitis (JE) virus and cases occur sporadically there. Although the conditions under which the affected individuals acquired their JE infections are not given, it is likely to have been in an agricultural area where the mosquito vectors are common at this time of year and birds that are the reservoir hosts are present and breeding. Transmission of JE virus will continue until the 1st killing frosts of autumn occur. - Mod.TY

